Metadata-Version: 1.1
Name: analyze-site
Version: 0.1.3
Summary: Utility to crawl web site looking for key words
Home-page: https://github.com/OV105/site-analyzer
Author: Tim Lee
Author-email: timhl81@gmail.com
License: Apache 2.0
Description: analyze_site is a python application to crawl a site and return a count of the keywords, provided in a file, found in the web pages of the site. The application will also return counts of the most used verb, nouns, adverbs and adjectives.
        
        analyze_site requires Python version 3 and the following libraries:
        
        * nltk - Natural Language Toolkit with maxent_treebank_pos_tagger
        
        
        
        usage: analyze_site.py [-h] [-d DEPTH] [-r PATH_REGEX] [--verbose]
                               keywords_file url
        
        positional arguments:
          keywords_file         Path to keywords file
          url                   URL to crawl
        
        optional arguments:
          -h, --help            show this help message and exit
          -d DEPTH, --depth DEPTH
                                Depth to crawl
          -r PATH_REGEX, --path_regex PATH_REGEX
                                Regular expression to match URL
          --verbose             Increase logging level
        
        
Keywords: web,crawl,analyze
Platform: UNKNOWN
